												<tr> 
													<td> 
<P>
<a name="a203"></a>
<table width="100%" cellpadding="1">
  <tr>
    <td valign="top">
      <br><div class="itemTitle"><b></b></div><U><FONT face="Geneva,Arial,Sans-<U"><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif size=3><STRONG>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif><FONT size=3><U><STRONG>The Crew of the&nbsp;<EM>Mea<SPAN style="COLOR: yellow">ly</SPAN> T<SPAN style="COLOR: yellow">owel</SPAN></EM>&nbsp;</STRONG></U></FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"></STRONG></FONT></U>&nbsp;</P><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif><FONT size=2>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">After an extensive externship with Dr. Claus Horof in which Yellow Team members successfully returned Cygnan Trelix Saratreet to her home planet, the members of the Yellow Team dispersed to pursue their own fortunes in the galaxy: 
<P></P></SPAN>
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">
<P></SPAN><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Steve Bush</SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> rose through the ranks of the Gholanian Ministry of State, where he became fluent in over three hundred organic and machine languages and later designed a prototype for the Universal Translator (now standard equipment for all Gholanian diplomats).<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>He also successfully negotiated a truce to the centuries-long Xlala - Protalon conflict by using his psychic powers to convince each side that it had successfully wiped out the other; the Xhalans and the Protalons now live and work in the same star system unaware of each others’ existence.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</SPAN>Bush is currently serving as a Justice on the Intergalactic Court of Human Rights, and recently issued a decision condemning the Ywakan practice of severing the third head of members of their lower caste at birth.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>His special powers include the ability to construct a functioning starship using nothing but small bits of rock, a Bic pen, and a kilogram of plutonium.</P>
<P></P></SPAN>
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">
<P></SPAN><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Christine Chang</SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> served for a short period as the Chief Navigator on the <I style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Hyberia</I>, a Cruiser-class luxury space liner, but was abruptly dismissed when she split open the skull of the pilot for “not turning fast enough” to the proper coordinates.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>She later became the first Terran to successfully climb the volcanic Mt. Dala using only her teeth, and she currently teaches yoga and mind-meld techniques to all three sentient species on the planet Shola.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Her special skills include mastery of thirty different classical musical instruments (including the Flen harp and the bassoon), and the recurring ability to lactate for short periods of time on demand.<SPAN style="COLOR: blue"> </P>
<P></P></SPAN></SPAN>
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">
<P></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">After years of successful collaboration with his Yellow Team colleagues, <B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">Ron Keesing</B> fell into an interdimensional portal and disappeared for nearly ten years.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>He spent most of the time trapped in a subterranean dungeon on the planet Yokka, where he passed the time honing his numerous extra-sensory abilities, constructing an alternate proof for Fermat’s Last Theorem, and inventing an improved translight hyperdrive mechanism.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Keesing escaped captivity amidst the chaos of the Great Yokkan Rebellion of ’04, and currently resides on the mountainous planet Viyad, where he is studying the feeding habits of various Viyadian insects.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>He possesses a photographic memory of all Dulanian poetry and has the ability to fly short distances in low-gravity environments.</P>
<P></P></SPAN>
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">
<P></SPAN><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Eric LeVine</SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> became a fighter pilot for the Fuzra rebellion during their 1999 uprising against the Galactic Empire.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>After the rebellion was crushed and the Fuzra race exterminated, LeVine became a smuggler of fermented grape beverages and other contraband, working the lucrative Qanto-Sdara route and regularly consulting the Mooncursor’s Handbook 41<SUP>st</SUP> Edition.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Last year in order to evade patrol ships, he was forced to land on the primitive planet of Griwaca, whose inch-tall inhabitants began worshipping him as a god.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>He currently resides in one of his sixty-seven temples on Griwaca, where he lives a life of pampered luxury.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>His special skills include the ability to kill a full-grown Zradabeast with his bare hands and fluency of the ancient Ngo language.</P>
<P></P></SPAN>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">
<P></SPAN><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">James Porter</SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> joined the Imperial Engineering Corps and was dispatched to the Outer Rim, where in a matter of three years he built up a spectacular reputation, overseeing the successful terraforming and colonization of a record seventeen planets on six different star systems.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Unfortunately his eighteenth project suffered a setback when he was attacked by Vegan Brain Parasites during a critical moment of the procedure, leading to the accidental supernova of the star and destruction of the entire system.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Porter miraculously survived the encounter and recuperated at the Sladdian Resort and Spa in the Ulurian quandrant, where he mastered the ancient sport of shuffleboard.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>He currently runs a Flivvery plantation in the Tynkan system; his special skills include the ability to lift ten times his body weight and project an astral image of himself over twenty parsecs away.</P>
<P></P></SPAN>
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">
<P></SPAN><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Ric Simmons</SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> spent a few years as Supreme Master and Overlord of the Wadono sector of the galaxy.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>His political career was cut short by scandal when a subspace periodical revealed that he was actually a six-legged alien from the planet Dobnos.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>His former colleagues on the Yellow Team were not surprised by the revelation, having noticed his ability to breathe through his armpits and his predilection for eating baby crickets.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Simmons now has plans to open up an intergalactic cantina, complete with Arcanian Mud Wrestling contests.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>His special skills include the ability to see three seconds into the future and making a delicious chocolate Gowana Bean souffl&eacute;.</SPAN></P></FONT></FONT><BR>
<P><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif size=2></FONT></P>
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">
<P><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif><FONT size=3><U><STRONG>The <EM>Mea<SPAN style="COLOR: yellow">ly</SPAN> T<SPAN style="COLOR: yellow">owel</SPAN></EM>&nbsp;</STRONG></U></FONT></FONT></P>
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">
<P><STRONG><U><FONT face=Arial size=3></FONT></U></STRONG></P><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif><FONT size=2>In early 2005, the Yellow Team reunited and together purchased a small ship, christened the <I style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Mealy Towel,</I> to conduct clandestine missions throughout the galaxy.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes"> </SPAN><I style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">The Mealy Towel </I>is small but extraordinarily maneuverable, and can make the Kessel run in less than twelve parsecs.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN></FONT></FONT>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes"><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif size=2></FONT></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes"></SPAN><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif size=2>The outer hull of the ship is pure Corbomite, a material and device which creates a reverse reaction whenever any destructive energy touches the ship, destroying the attacker.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Of course, the ship’s cloaking device generally keeps it from being detected, except when firing its sub-atomic neutro destabilizer or detonating an electromagnetic pulse. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif size=2>The <I style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Mealy Towel’s </I>primary means of propulsion is the ship’s Improbability Drive, which is currently generating extraordinary amounts of energy by the chances of any other team winning the interstellar contest that we expect will be an integral part of the August release party. <SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</SPAN>Once the probability of victory reaches 1, backup propulsion will be provided by a compact Beryllium Sphere Hyperdrive. </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif size=2>The ship is equipped with Heuristic Algorithmic 9000, an advanced artificial intelligence unit which controls everything from basic life support to closing and opening the pod bay doors and can hum a nifty version of “Daisy”.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The system’s psychohistory module regularly predicts the course of interstellar affairs, and has correctly predicted the <SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</SPAN>fall of the Galactic Empire, although it still can’t explain the results of the 2004 Terran elections. Leon, the ship’s robot, has flexible arms that can be flailed wildly to signal danger and sophisticated auditory circuitry capable of emitting repeated warning signals. Of course, he only notices on those rare occasions when he’s not struck by a paralyzing bout of depression.</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif size=2>Other features of the ship include neuralyzer for erasing the memories of civilians who might catch the crew in compromising situations, and a fully functional electronic synthesizer for playing music to primitive civilizations that we might encounter.&nbsp;</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif><FONT size=2>The ship is currently docked at Moonbase Alpha, where it is <SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</SPAN>receiving numerous upgrades and improvements in preparation for the upcoming release party.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Engineer Porter is working on a Sleep Deprivation Removal Chamber, complete with intravenous caffeine drip and continuous electroshock stimulus.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Captain Bush and Navigator Chang are developing a Team Mind Meld Chamber which can hold every member of the crew and pool their brainpower together in order to solve any puzzles or challenges the crew might face.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Pilot LeVine has purchased a Hyperspace Accelerator Enforcement Detector in case the InterGalactic Space Patrol is monitoring the velocity of our ship during the event.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN></FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif><FONT size=2><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes"></SPAN></FONT></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif><FONT size=2><I style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Mealy Towel </I>is scheduled to touch down at SeaTac at the posted coordinates on August 19<SUP>th</SUP>.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN></FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes"></SPAN>
<P></P><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif size=2></FONT>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">
<P><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif size=3><STRONG><U>Ship’s Log, <I style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Mea<SPAN style="COLOR: yellow">ly</SPAN> T<SPAN style="COLOR: yellow">owel</SPAN>,</I> Stingray class transport ship</U></STRONG></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">
<P><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P></P><FONT color=white>
<P></P><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif><FONT size=2>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: white; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Stardate</SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: white; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> -316836.16<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>
<P></P></SPAN>
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: white; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Touched down on recently colonized planet in response to distress call, but found settlement abandoned except for a large cluster of eggs being stored for an unknown purpose.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Upon closer examination, one egg cracked and small reptilian creature attacked itself to Engineer Porter’s faceplate.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Reptilian creature was removed in sick bay, and Porter seems none the worse for wear, although he was complaining of stomach pains during dinner. 
<P></P></SPAN>
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: white; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">
<P>&nbsp;</P></SPAN>
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: white; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Stardate</SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: white; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> -316812.77 
<P></P></SPAN>
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: white; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Shipboard sensors picked up signs of heavy combat on the surface of planet Klendathu. Further analysis revealed a fascist army attempting to invade and wipe out the Arachnid race. Although capable of interstellar travel, the fascists had apparently only brought along rifles and hand grenades as their weapons, while the Arachnids’ primary method of attack was to hurl enormous meteors at the fascist’s home planet. <SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</SPAN>After brief observation the decision was made not to intervene, which though justified by the “Prime Directive”, was really due to the fact that we found both sides to be so unpalatable that we preferred watching them wipe each other out. 
<P></P></SPAN>
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: white; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">
<P>&nbsp;</P></SPAN>
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: white; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Stardate</SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: white; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> -316793.12 
<P></P></SPAN>
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: white; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">St. Patrick’s Day celebration cut short when <I style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Mealy Towel </I>was attacked by swarm of small fighter ships piloted by silver robots with red lights for eyes that constantly panned from left to right.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Most of the crew was too intoxicated to respond, but Crewman Keesing was able to stumble to the communications console and establish contact. Between laser blasts, the robot in charge explained they were searching for a “rag-tag fugitive Colonial fleet” of humans in order to eliminate them from the galaxy.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Crewman Keesing was able to convince the robots that we were not in fact humans but that we had just seen a large fleet of human ships at the last spaceport.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>“You just missed them,” he explained in a somewhat slurred voice, “but if you hurry over there you might be able to catch them before they make their next hyperspace jump.”<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The robotic fleet disappeared immediately and we returned to our victuals. 
<P></P></SPAN>
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: white; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">
<P>&nbsp;</P></SPAN>
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: white; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Stardate</SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: white; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> -316790.36 
<P></P></SPAN>
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: white; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Landing on the inconsequential and mostly harmless planet Thrae, the crew discovered that the entire population had been wiped out by a large, hairy creature wearing a diving helmet and calling himself “Extension XJ-2 of the Ro-Men.” The terrible beast’s bubble machine seemed to spell sure doom to the crew, but just when all seemed lost, the furry beast became smitten with Navigator Chang, leading to his destruction by “The Great Guidance.” The entire episode was then revealed to be a daydream of Pilot LeVine, who had bonked his head during an ill-advised attempt to somersault over the Orlynxian Glurball Table. LeVine was severely reprimanded for carelessness, as well as for dreaming up something that would make Ed Wood cringe. 
<P></P></SPAN>
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: white; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">
<P>&nbsp;</P></SPAN>
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: white; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Stardate</SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: white; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> -316788.22 
<P></P></SPAN>
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><I style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: white; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Mealy Towel </SPAN></I><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: white; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">was caught in the tractor beam of an enormous ship in the shape of a cube.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>After explaining that resistance was futile, the enemy ship kidnapped Crewman Simmons and assimilated him into their race.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Captain Bush led a daring rescue attempt into the cube and returned Simmons to the <I style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Towel</I>, where he returned to his normal duties in his assimilated state. <I style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</SPAN></I>Aside from his rather annoying insistence at being called “Voman of Borg, Tertiary Adjunct of Unimatrix Zero-One,” the crew has not noticed any appreciable change in his behavior.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: white; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">
<P></P></SPAN>&nbsp; 
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"></FONT></FONT></FONT><FONT color=white><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif><FONT size=2>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif><SPAN style="COLOR: white">
<P></P></SPAN></FONT></FONT></FONT></FONT></FONT>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><STRONG><U><FONT size=3>Crew Qualifications</FONT></U></STRONG></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">Steve Bush</B><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"> </B></FONT>
<UL style="MARGIN-TOP: 0in" type=disc>
<LI class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in"><FONT face=Geneva,Arial,Sans-Serif>Played in </FONT>
<UL style="MARGIN-TOP: 0in" type=circle>
